The word meus was treated much in the same way as deus: we have therefore mei mac mco meos meas mei-3 sometimes as monosyllableS, and meorum mearum as disyllables ¹. The real pronunciation of these forms· in such cases may be ascertained from the spelling micis (ἐπιθῶ) which occurs in the dactylic inscription on the sepulchre of one of the Scipios: this enables us to guess that it was probably very much like the modern' Greek pronunciation of θιός (= θεὰς), i.e. myas dyo, dvc.
